msgid ""
"The peer object to handle the RPC system (effectively enabling networking"
" when set). Depending on the peer itself, the ``SceneTree`` will become a"
" network server (check with :ref:`is_network_server "
"<class_SceneTree_method_is_network_server>`) and will set the root node's"
" network mode to master, or it will become a regular peer with the root "
"node set to puppet. All child nodes are set to inherit the network mode "
"by default. Handling of networking-related events (connection, "
"disconnection, new clients) is done by connecting to ``SceneTree``'s "
"signals."
msgstr ""
"对等对象用于处理RPC系统（设置后有效地启用联网）。取决于对等本身，``SceneTree`` 将成为网络服务端（使用 "
":ref:`is_network_server <class_SceneTree_method_is_network_server>` "
"检查），并将根节点的网络模式设置为 ``master`` （参见 :ref:`Node <class_Node>` 中的 "
"``NETWORK_MODE_*`` 常量）；否则它将成为根节点设置为 ``puppet`` "
"的常规对等。默认情况下，所有子节点都设置为继承网络模式。通过连接到 ``SceneTree`` "
"的信号，来处理与网络相关的事件（连接、断开连接、新建客户端）。"

